  "content": "green);\">&#8635;</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 24px; color: var(--accent-green); font-weight: 600;\">Feedback loop</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div style=\"display: flex; align-items: center; font-size: 48px; color: var(--text-muted);\">vs</div>\n    <div style=\"flex: 1; text-align: center;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 56px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">&#129302;</div>\n      <h3 style=\"font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px;\">AI Code Agent</h3>\n      <div style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 14px;\">\n        <div style=\"background: rgba(59,130,246,0.15); border: 1px solid rgba(59,130,246,0.3); border-radius: 12px; padding: 16px 28px; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; width: 90%;\">Write CSS</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 28px; color: var(--accent-red);\">&#8595;</div>\n        <div style=\"background: rgba(239,68,68,0.15); border: 2px dashed var(--accent-red); border-radius: 12px; padding: 16px 28px; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; width: 90%; color: var(--accent-red);\">&#128683; Can't see output</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 28px; color: var(--accent-red);\">&#8595;</div>\n        <div style=\"background: rgba(239,68,68,0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(239,68,68,0.2); border-radius: 12px; padding: 16px 28px; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; width: 90%; color: var(--text-muted);\">Hope it works?</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 28px; color: var(--accent-red);\">&#10060;</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 24px; color: var(--accent-red); font-weight: 600;\">No feedback loop</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"insight-box\">\n    <p>A human designer's superpower isn't better CSS &mdash;<br>\n    it's the ability to <strong>look at the screen and react</strong>.</p>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"flex-grow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">05 / 08</div>\n</div>",
